{
  "texts": [
    "1 Probe+pion interaction in RL truncation.",
    "Both panels.",
    "Solid lines -dressed quarks, S; orange shaded circles -pion Bethe-Salpeter amplitude, π; and blue shaded circles -dressed probe+quark vertex, P. Lower panel.",
    "Shaded C region -gluon-binding contribution to the probe+pion interaction, which vanishes for F π but cancels a Qlongitudinal contribution from the top diagram when computing the graviton+pion coupling, thereby ensuring cπ ≡ 0 in Eq.",
    "Analogous diagrams define the kaon form factors 2 u = 3."
  ]
